The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Ban on air horn
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Ban on air horn
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Air horns will be banned in Calcutta in a phased manner, transport minister Subhas Chakraborty said on Friday. Initially, air horns will be banned on BT Road, Diamond Harbour Road and Kona Expressway. From February 15, the ban will be enforced across the state, said the minister.        
	Man dead: Suraj Diyali, a 34-year-old Kalimpong resident, started vomiting blood in his friends Marquis Street residence early on Friday. He was pronounced dead at NRS Hospital.        
	Train trouble: Passengers of a Bongaon-bound local train from Sealdah handed over a 19-year-old Bangladeshi man to police on Friday, finding his movements suspicious.        
	Fog delay: Two flights to Dhaka were delayed on Friday because of fog there.        
	Research centre: A research centre for the Howrah foundry cluster was launched on the Jadavpur University campus on Friday.                                                                                                                                                                         
